<div class="content-wrapper">
  <div class="container">
    <section class="digital-marketing-service" id="rth-info-section">
      <div class="row align-items-center">
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-5 flex-item grid-margin grid-margin-lg-0" data-aos="fade-right">
          <h3 class="m-0">Flying with the Eagleville Soaring Club</h3>
          <div class="col-lg-9 col-xl-8 p-0">
            <p class="py-4 m-0 text-muted">Eagleville Soaring club offers non-members and glider novices the chance to fly in a glider
            and experience the wonder of non-powered flight. Our 'Red Tail Hawk' flights are a great introduction to soaring for people interested in club membership, 
            or perfect for anyone who wants to see the Middle Tennessee countryside from a different vantage point</p>
            <p class="font-weight-medium text-muted">Rides are dependent on weather, our flying schedule, and the availability of a pilot, but
            most weekends allow room for guests to fly with us. </p>
          </div>    
        </div>
        <div class="col-12 col-lg-7 p-0 img-digital grid-margin grid-margin-lg-0" data-aos="fade-left">
          <%= image_tag("tow_signals.jpeg", :alt => "", :class => "img-fluid") %>
        </div>
      </div>  
      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
          <%= link_to "Ask About a Glider Ride", new_email_request_path(query: 'ride'), :class => "btn btn-primary" %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>     
    <div class="container-fluid" style="background-color:#f7f8fa;">  
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row m-4 ">
            <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
              <li class="list-group-item lead pb-3" id='how-to-schedule' style="background-color:#f7f8fa;">              
                <d1 class="row">
                  <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Want to take a ride?</dt>
                    <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                      <p>The best way to experience soaring with us is to visit the field on a weekend. Since we
                      are entirely volunteer-operated, all flights depend on our instruction schedule, weather
                      conditions, and aircraft availability. While we love sharing the thrill of soaring, we can’t
                      guarantee rides on any given day.</p>
                    </dd>
                    <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">How to Visit</dt>
                    <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                      <p>We typically fly on weekends, weather permitting. If you’d like to stop by, we
                      recommend arriving in the morning and checking in with one of our members. While we
                      generally don’t take reservations for rides, visiting in person gives you the best chance
                      to see what’s possible for the day. We publish a banner on this website every day that
                      we are flying, and most days that we are not.</p>
                    </dd>
                    <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">What to expect when you arrive</dt>
                    <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                      <p>Visitors to the field may find our members spread out across the field, in the hangar, or in the office. We 
                      are usually easy to spot. If you have to look for us, please stay on the "safe" side of the runway cones nearer the 
                      road. <strong>The runway at Eagleville Soaring is always active!</strong></p>
                      <p>After the required waivers are signed and the rider has been weighed to ensure proper weight and balance of the glider, one of our members will escort you and your family members down to the flight line.
                      Here you will meet your pilot and go through a basic explanation of our safety protocols and flight expectations. </p>
                      <p>Once all that is out of the way, you and your pilot will get strapped into one of our Schleicher ASK-21 gliders and 
                      prepare for takeoff.</p> 
                      
                    </dd>
                    <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">What to expect during your flight</dt>
                    <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                      <p>Every flight begins with an "aerotow" up to altitude. Our line crew will secure the glider to the Piper Pawnee 
                      tow plane with a long rope and the tow plane will pull the rope tight. The tow pilot, glider pilot, and ground crew 
                      will all exchange hand signals to signal that they are ready for takeoff. The tow plane will apply power and accelerate until first the 
                      glider, and then the tow plane smoothly lift off the runway.</p>
                      <p>During the aerotow, your experienced glider pilot will be working to stay directly behind the tow plane. Once at altitude, usually around 3,000 feet above the ground
                      the glider pilot may ask you to pull the release handle and disconnect the tow rope from the glider. Now you are gliding!</p> 
                      <p>The length of a glider flight is dependent on many factors, including tow height, weather, and how busy the schedule is.
                      On many days, warm rising air from the ground creates enough upward momentum that a glider can slow down and turn in the rising air. Using these
                      'thermals' we are able to gain altitude even though the gliders don't have engines. When this happens, you aren't just gliding, now you are soaring!</p>

                    </dd>
                    <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">After the flight</dt>
                    <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                      <p>Once the flight is over, you and your family are welcome to stay and
                      watch the glider operations at Eagleville Soaring. Don't be surprised if your first flight turns into a 
                      desire to join our club. Many of our members began the same way.</p>
                      <p>Payment for a Red Tail Hawk ride can be made via check or cash at the office on the field, or via credit card
                      using the QR Code located in the office on the field post-ride.</p> 
                      
                    </dd>
                    <dt class="col-sm-4 ps-4 pt-2">Requirements for all riders</dt>
                    <dd class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                      <ul class="col-sm-8 pt-2">
                        <li>All riders require a signed waiver</li>
                        <li>Riders must be weighed before flying to ensure proper distribution of ballast in the glider</li>
                        <li>Riders are limited to 242 lbs and may be height limited if significantly above 6 feet tall</li>
                        <li>Ride cost is $180, payable after the flight</li>
                      </ul>
                    </dd>
                  </d1> 
              </ul>     
              
            </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>    
      </div>
    </div>
    
